  "response": "Here's the step-by-step procedure for becoming a Chartered Accountant (CA) after 12th:\n\n1. Educational Qualification\n- Complete 12th standard from a recognized board\n- Choose Commerce stream preferably\n\n2. CA Foundation Course\n- Register with ICAI (Institute of Chartered Accountants of India)\n- Appear for CA Foundation Exam\n- Minimum age: 21 years\n\n3. Foundation Course Requirements\n- Online registration on ICAI website\n- Pay registration fees\n- Pass foundation exam\n- Valid for 4 attempts within 2 years\n\n4. CA Intermediate Course\n- Enroll for Intermediate Course\n- Choose study mode: Self-study or Coaching\n- Study prescribed syllabus\n- Appear for Intermediate Exam\n- Two groups of papers\n\n5. Articleship Training\n- Complete 3-year practical training\n- Mandatory internship with CA firm\n- Gain practical accounting experience\n\n6. CA Final Exam\n- Appear for CA Final Examination\n- Comprehensive professional knowledge test\n- Consists of two groups of papers\n\n7. Additional Requirements\n- IELTS/English proficiency\n- Computer knowledge\n- Good communication skills\n\nFinal step: Get CA membership after completing all requirements.",
